                Any references to Commodore stockholders, living or deceased,
                is purely coincidental.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node FAQ.Software.3.06 "Software Questions 2.017"
@toc FAQ.Software

    3.06 May I use one package on two computers?

            If you own two computers, in most cases you are not allowed
        to use the same software on both computers unless one of the
        following guidelines is met:


            1. Both computers will not be running the same software
               license at the same time.

            2. Both computers have individually purchased software
               packages, independent of the other copy.

            3. The owner may have a license to use more than one copy,
               with the number of copies specified in the site license.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node FAQ.Software.3.07 "Software Questions"
@version 2.091
@toc FAQ.Software

    3.07 How can I secure a copyright or trademark?

            To secure a copyright, you may place the ｩ symbol and
        the word COPYRIGHT before the year of creation and the
        company/owner. All computer or art is considered copyrighted
        upon creation. However, to receive a legally binding
        document from the US Government, you must fill out the proper
        forms, costing approximately $20. If you wish to have a
        trademarked name, which reserves it for your use only, you
        may reference the list of trademarked names to search for
        an original name. If your name is unused, you may file for
        a trademark for approximately $175. Trademarked names can be
        local or national. Call the US Trademark Office at
        (703) 308-4357 for more information.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
